Take a look at your domain objects, it looks like you have the CustomerD pointing to his/her OrdersD and the OrdersD pointing to the CustomerD. As far as I can understand, the strong relationship is between the CoustomerD -&gt; OrdersD and the reference from the OrderD to the CustomerD looks like just something convenient for you. 

In this case, the OrderD mapper should not create a new CustomerD by itself. Doing this will duplicate entities (each order will generate a new instance of the CustomerD), and that is not what you want.

Just create a new method for OrderMapper that just maps the Order:

    public class OrderMapper {
    
      @Inject
      ProductMapper productMapper;
        
      @Inject
      CustomerMapper customerMapper;

      public OrderD mapEntityToDomainJustEntity(final OrderT orderT) {
        final OrderD orderD = new OrderD();
        orderD.setId(orderT.getOrderId());
        return orderD;
      }

      public OrderD mapEntityToDomain(final OrderT orderT) {
        final OrderD orderD = mapEntityToDomainJustEntity(orderT);         
        orderD.setCustomerD(customerMapper.mapEntityToDomain(orderT.getCustomerT()));
        return orderD;
      }

