The framework should work independently without being bound to your current application. 

The best way to achieve this would be to use the delegate pattern for your application to respond to events triggered from the framework. An example below for a user logging into the application

So you could do something like this:

    protocol ABCFrameworkProfileDelegate: AnyObject {
        func userDidLogin()
        func authenticationFailed(withError: Error)
    }

Then in your application:

    import ABCFramework
    
    // maybe on button tap?
    let authService = ABCAuthService()
    authService.login(username: &quot;user&quot;, password: &quot;pwd&quot;)
    
    // once the login request completes either this or the failed method should be called.
    func userDidLogin() {
        let vc = FirstViewController() 
        push(vc, animated: true)
    }

This way your application can manage which views to show based on what events occur.

Based on what you&#39;ve used, you can create a custom attribute in your styles such as:

    &lt;style name=&quot;MyTheme&quot; parent=&quot;@style/ThemeOverlay.AppCompat.Dark&quot;&gt;
        &lt;item name=&quot;recyclerViewBackground&quot;&gt;@drawable/paywall_background&lt;/item&gt;
    &lt;/style&gt;

    &lt;style name=&quot;MyTheme2&quot; parent=&quot;@style/ThemeOverlay.AppCompat.Dark&quot;&gt;
        &lt;item name=&quot;recyclerViewBackground&quot;&gt;@drawable/another_background&lt;/item&gt;
    &lt;/style&gt;

Add this to your **attrs.xml** file under **values** folder (if you don&#39;t have it, create it):

    &lt;attr name=&quot;recyclerViewBackground&quot; format=&quot;reference&quot; /&gt;

And set the background using this:

    &lt;com.airbnb.epoxy.EpoxyRecyclerView
        style=&quot;?theme&quot;
        android:id=&quot;@+id/recycler_view&quot;
        android:layout_width=&quot;match_parent&quot;
        android:layout_height=&quot;match_parent&quot; 
        android:background=&quot;?recyclerViewBackground&quot;/&gt;

Changing the theme and **recreating the fragment** should change the background of the `RecyclerView` now. Also make sure every theme you will use with this view includes the attribute `recyclerViewBackground` otherwise you will get an exception.

